\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 2. G. linifolia} Vahl,{\i  Enum. Pl.}{\b  1}: 89 (1804). Like {\b 1} but glandular-puberulent at least above; stems terete; leaves linear, more or less entire; pedicels at least as long as subtending leaves.{\i  Ditches, river-banks and marshes. • Portugal, S.W. Spain.} Hs Lu.
